## 1. What I=E2=80=99m Trying to Do (Business Requirements)

I=E2=80=99ve built a series of GPT-based leadership and business tools (Valu=
es Architect, Mission Architect, People Analyzer, Leadership Day GPT, etc.) t=
hat help business owners clarify vision, align teams, and drive execution.

Right now they exist as individual GPTs and workflows.

My goal is to turn this into a structured, subscription-based application =E2=
=80=94 essentially a Leadership Operating System for small to mid-sized busi=
ness owners.

The app should:

- Help owners clarify mission, vision, values
- Translate those into dashboards, goals, and accountability
- Provide guided leadership workflows
- Track team alignment and performance over time
- Feel like a =E2=80=9Cliving operating system,=E2=80=9D not a one-off chatb=
ot

Revenue Model:
- Monthly subscription (tiered)
- Potential group/enterprise pricing
- Long-term possibility of licensing to consultants

---

## 2. What the App Needs to Do (Functional Requirements)

Core Functional Components:

### A. Structured AI Modules
Each GPT becomes a guided workflow inside the app:
- Core Values Builder
- Mission Builder
- Vision Builder
- People Analyzer
- Leadership Development Planner
- Quarterly Planning System
- Meeting System (L10-style)
- 360 Feedback Builder
- Talent Review System

These should:
- Save progress
- Persist data across sessions
- Store answers in structured format
- Feed dashboards automatically

---

### B. Dashboards

The system needs dashboards that:
- Display company mission, vision, and values
- Show quarterly goals and progress
- Display team alignment scores (from People Analyzer)
- Show performance and accountability data
- Track leadership growth over time

This should feel like:
- A clean executive dashboard
- Simple, powerful, visual
- Not cluttered

---

### C. Multi-User Functionality

Eventually:
- Owner login
- Leadership team access
- Role-based permissions
- Team-level data segmentation

---

### D. Payment & Subscription

- Monthly recurring billing
- Different tiers (Solo, Leadership Team, Enterprise)
- Stripe or equivalent integration

---

## 3. Where I Want This Available (Technical Requirements)

Phase 1:
- Web-based application
- Mobile responsive

Phase 2:
- Native mobile app (if needed)

Must have:
- Secure login
- Cloud data storage
- AI API integration (OpenAI, Claude, or hybrid)
- Scalable architecture

---

## 4. What I Already Have

I currently have:

- Fully built GPT workflows with defined prompts and logic
- Branded framework (Aligned Growth / AGOS philosophy)
- Structured leadership models and exercises
- Existing paying consulting clients
- Clear ICP: business owners doing $1M=E2=80=93$20M revenue
- Content library (mission systems, people analyzer scoring, etc.)
- Defined methodology for leadership development

What I do NOT yet have:
- Unified data structure
- Persistent database layer
- Dashboard framework
- Payment system

---

## 5. Where I Want to Start

I want to start with a focused MVP.

Phase 1 MVP:
- Mission + Values Builder
- Quarterly Planning Tool
- Simple Executive Dashboard
- User login + saved data
- Stripe billing
- Clean UX

If that works and gets traction, we layer in:
- People Analyzer
- 360 system
- Leadership scorecards
- Multi-user permissions

---

